land====\n{{Scottish Constituency Election box begin | title=Scottish Parliament general election, 2011: [[North East Scotland (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|North East Scotland]]}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n{{Scottish Electoral Area Election box begin | title=[[2007 Scottish Parliament election]]: North East Scotland}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n====South Scotland====\n\n{{Scottish Constituency Election box begin | title=Scottish Parliament general election, 2011: [[South Scotland (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|South Scotland]]}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n====West of Scotland====\n\n{{Scottish Constituency Election box begin | title=Scottish Parliament general election, 2011: [[West of Scotland (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|West of Scotland]]}}\n{{Election box end}}\n-->\n\n== Opinion polling ==\n=== Constituency vote ===\n{{main|Opinion polling for the next Scottish Parliament election#Constituency vote}}\n[[File:Opinion polling for the next Scottish Parliament election (constituency vote).svg]]\n\n=== Regional vote ===\n{{main|Opinion polling for the next Scottish Parliament election#Regional vote}}\n[[File:Opinion polling for the next Scottish Parliament election (regional vote).svg]]\n\n==Target seats==\nBelow are listed all the constituencies which require a [[Swing (United Kingdom)|swing]] of less than 5% from the 2016 results to change hands.\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-2}}\n\n===SNP targets===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:550px\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:50px;\"|Rank\n! style=\"width:225px;\"|Constituency\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:175px;\"|Winning party 2016\n! style=\"width:100px;\"|Swing to gain\n! style=\"width:100px;\"|SNP's place 2016\n! style=\"width:100px;\"|Result\n|-\n|1\n|[[Dumbarton (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Dumbarton]]\n{{party name with colour|Scottish Labour Party}}\n|0.17\n|2nd\n|\n|-\n|2\n|[[Edinburgh Central (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Edinburgh Central]]\n{{party name with colour|Scottish Conservati