{"title_page": "Craig Healy", "text_new": "{{short description|Olympic sailor from the United States}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Craig Healy<ref name=\"Sports-Reference\" />\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| native_name    = \n| birth_name     =  \n| fullname       =  Craig Jon Healy\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{USA}}\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1957|9|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[San Pablo, California]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{convert|1.85|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = \n| classes        = [[Soling]]\n| club           = [[San Francisco Yacht Club]]\n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = 1 March 2020\n}}\n\n'''Craig Healy''' (born: 9 September 1957) is a sailor from [[San Pablo, California]], [[United States]]. who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]], [[Australia]] as crew member in the [[Soling]]. With helmsman [[Jeff Madrigali]] and fellow crew member [[Hartwell Jordan]] they took the 9th place.<ref name=\"OS2000\" /> \n{{Footer North American Champions Soling}}\n{{Authority control}}\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n  <ref name = Sports-Reference>{{cite web\n                                  |url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20121114134805/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/he/craig-healy-1.html\n                                  |title      = Craig Healy Bio, Stats, and Results \n                                  |publisher  = Sports-Reference.com \n                                  |work       = Olympic Sports \n                                  |accessdate = 1 March 2020 \n                                  |url-status = live\n                                  |df=dmy \n                                }}</ref>\n  <ref name = OS2000>{{cit